    <briefdescription>
<para>Lookup strategy using a flat vector with linear scan. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>`LinearLookupStrategy` stores strong IDs in a contiguous vector and performs linear scans for membership tests. Swap-and-pop is used for O(1) removal. Suitable for small registries where hash overhead is undesirable.</para>
<para><parameterlist kind="templateparam"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>TCapacity</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Default initial capacity for pre-allocation.</para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
